data.title: Club at Starr Pass
data.description: 27-holes of championship desert golf at your fingertips. Golf legends such as Arnold Palmer, Phil Mickelson, Payne Stewart and Nancy Lopez, to name a few, have all carved their way through this historic golf course. Today the legend continues as Arnold Palmer completed a redesign of the original 18-hole Cupp/Stadler layout and added a new nine holes making Starr Pass a 27-hole Championship Golf Course. The course is a true desert experience as all of the hazards are completely natural elements of the environment. The three nines, which wind their way through the mountains and arroyos, are aptly named after the ever-present desert wildlife: Rattler, Road Runner and Coyote. Starr Pass Golf Club was the host facility for the PGA Tour’s Tucson Open from 1988 to 1995.

data.title: 611 Pub, Inc.
data.description: Fantastic venue! The outdoor seating is such a vibe come summer. Nice bright open space for dining with a variety of tabletops - high, low, comfy big couches/chairs. Downstairs contains the bowling alley

data.title: A Cottage At Campbell Farm
data.description: 4 romantic, secluded cottages in the Mountains; full equipped kitchens, gas fireplaces, 2 person Jacuzzi tubs - BBQ grill on deck. Very quiet and peaceful; no TV or telephone. Have recently opened the Log House; it is for couples that like to travel together; 2 master suites upstairs, but sharing the kitchen, living room, and dining areas. Only have to bring your food; everything else is provided.

data.title: Anthony's Longfellow Hotel
data.description: We welcome kids and adults with an indoor pool, free Internet and a free, hot breakfast.

data.title: Big Shot Bob's
data.description: We serve a variety of food here at Big Shot Bobs House Of Wings. Our menu offers Cheeseburgers, Bacon Ranch Cheese Fries, Rodeo, Chicken Fingers, The Jimmy DeTillo and more! We are located North Wickham Road. We're not far from ALDI. Order online for carryout or delivery!

data.title: Freddy's Frozen Custard
data.description: Freddy's Frozen Custard & Steakburgers is more than your traditional American hamburger restaurant. We are known for our tasty steakburgers and custards.

data.title: Hopwood Motel
data.description: Family owned and operated, Uniontown's closest lodging to Falling Water, Ohiopyle, Laurel Caverns, Ft Necessity. Clean comfortable rooms, reasonably priced.

data.title: M G Motel
data.description: Lovely modern hotel with nice pool and amazing beach access. Good location with a few bars and restaurants near by and a short walk to the free trolly bus

data.title: National Trail Motel
data.description: This property is an ambient hotel of 35 units in a 2-story classic art-deco building. Included is a sparkling clear heated pool with waterfall, BBQ facilities, serene lounging area and a sun deck. We offer free Cable TV on a flat-screen TV, featuring HBO, free WiFi internet, and hot coffee at the Front Desk. A tropical oasis-style scenery is featured throughout our beautiful properties. We have an attentive staff available 24 hours.

data.title: Astorris Tavern
data.description: Astorris Tavern is a local bar filled with fun, friendly people just havin' a cold one.

data.title: Curt's Family Restaurant
data.description: Curt's Family Restaurant serves home cooked meals for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Pies and bakery are popular.

data.title: Crossroads Inn
data.description: Gorgeously designed rooms and suites help define the Crossroads experience. But more, this is where historic and modern meet. Where people from all over and around the corner come together. The energy, creativity and passion that define the city and neighborhood can call this place home.

data.title: Perry-O Inn & Suites
data.description: See why so many travelers make Perry-O Inn & Suites their motel of choice when visiting Perryopolis. Providing an ideal mix of value, comfort and convenience, it offers an array of amenities designed for travelers like you.
